{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781683017,"nonce":"JIGWXOzJPKEyu7VtScVLM/2DCOA=","title":"Join coverage: RIGHT / FULL OUTER / CROSS joins and self-joins","message":"Only INNER (join) and LEFT (left_join) joins exist in `crates/squealy/src/query.rs`. Missing:\n\n- right_join (RIGHT OUTER)\n- full_join (FULL OUTER) — note nullability: a FULL join makes columns from BOTH sides nullable in the projection, which the projection type machinery must reflect.\n- cross_join (CROSS, no ON clause).\n- Self-join: joining the same table twice requires distinct source aliases for the two instances; confirm/support aliasing the same Table type more than once in a query.\n\nLeft_join already established the pattern of widening the joined sides projection to Option\u003cT\u003e; right/full need the symmetric/both-sides widening. The source-alias machinery (SourceAlias in expr.rs) is the place self-join aliasing lands.","files":null}]}